OL,3,CPolice officer injured after being
OL,4,C'intentionally' struck by vehicle
OL,6,FHe got out to speak to the occupants,
OL,7,Fbut the vehicle's driver refused to
OL,8,Fspeak to him and then drove off,
OL,9,Fintentionally striking the officer as
OL,10,Fthey left.
OL,12,FThis injured the officer, who received
OL,13,Ftreatment at hospital and is now
OL,14,Frecovering at home.
OL,16,FDuty Superintendent Conway Duncan,
OL,17,Ffrom Wiltshire Police, said: "This is
OL,18,Fa significant incident where an
OL,19,Fofficer undertaking their duties has
OL,20,Fintentionally been injured by the
OL,21,Fdriver of the vehicle.
